Thousands of revellers will be heading to the Durban shore to ring in the New Year. DURBAN - Thousands of revellers will be heading to the Durban shore to ring in the New Year. Traffic is rising and beaches across the city are expected to be packed. Police have brought in more officers to control the crowds and keep tabs on criminal activity. Officers on foot, bikesÂ and the mounted unit are all patrolling the beachfront. Durban Metro Police spokesperson Parboo Sewpersad said their deployment plan is going well thus far. "We are ready for tonight. We understand that tonight there are many events hosted in the city," he said. "We are going to be policing all these events." People have descended onto the Durban beach front as New Year's Eve celebrations begin.